2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\"|29th [[Seoul Music Awards]]\n| Dance Performance Award\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"3\"|<ref name=\"sma2020\">{{cite web |author1=Ilin Mathew |title=Seoul Music Awards 2020 nomination list, live streaming details and more |url=https://www.ibtimes.sg/seoul-music-awards-2020-nomination-list-live-streaming-details-more-35686 |website=International Business Times, Singapore Edition |accessdate=January 31, 2020 |language=en |date=December 9, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| Hallyu Special Award\n| rowspan=\"3\" {{NA}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Popularity Award\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| QQ Music Most Popular K-Pop Artist Award\n| {{nom}}\n| <ref>{{cite web |url=https://y.qq.com/m/act/sma/index.html |work=QQ Music |title=\u7b2c29\u5c4aSMA-QQ\u97f3\u4e50\u6700\u53d7\u6b22\u8fceK-POP ARTIST\u5956 |language=zh |accessdate=January 31, 2020|archive-date=January 31, 2020|archive-url=http://archive.today/2020.01.31-105902/https://y.qq.com/m/act/sma/index.html}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http://www.makeusent.com/html/dh_board/views/65?/}}\n\n{{Sunmi}}\n{{Wonder Girls}}\n{{JYP Entertainment}}\n{{Mnet Asian Music Award for Best Female Artist}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:1992 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Wonder Girls members]]\n[[Category:Dongguk University alumni]]\n[[Category:JYP Entertainment artists]]\n[[Category:Mnet Asian Music Award winners]]\n[[Category:English-language singers from South Korea]]\n[[Category:Japanese-language singers of South Korea]]\n[[Category:Mandarin-language singers of South Korea]]\n[[Category:South Korean dance musicians]]\n[[Category:South Korean female idols]]\n[[Category:South Korean female pop singers]]\n[[Category:South Korean television personalities]]\n", "text_old": "{{Distinguish|Sonmi}}\n{{About|the singer|other people with this given name|Sun-mi (name)}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Short description|South Korean singer}}\n{{Korean name|Lee}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name             = Sunmi\n| image            = 190830 Sunmi KBS '\ubba4\uc9c1\ubc45\ud06c' 02.png\n| caption          = Sunmi in August 2019\n| image_size       =\n| native_name      = \uc774\uc120\ubbf8\n| birth_name       = Sun Mi\n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|1992|5|2}}\n| birth_place      = [[Iksan]], South Korea\n| education          = [[Dongguk University]]\n| occupation      = {{hlist|Singer|songwriter|}}\n\n| module          = {{Infobox musical artist|embed=yes\n| background       = solo_singer\n| genre            = {{hlist|[[K-pop]]|[[synth-pop]]|[[electropop]]|[[retro]]}}\n| instrument       = {{hlist|Vocals|bass guitar}}\n| years_active     = 2007\u20132010<br/>2013\u2013present\n| label            = {{hlist|[[JYP Entertainment|JYP]]|Makeus}}\n| associated_acts  = {{hlist|[[Wonder Girls]]|[[JYP Nation]]\n| website         =\n}}}}\n| module2          = {{Infobox Korean name\n| child           = yes\n| hangul          = {{linktext|\uc774|\uc120|\ubbf8}}\n| hanja           = {{linktext|\u674e|\u5ba3|\u7f8e}}\n| rr              = I Seon-mi\n| mr              = Ri S\u014fnmi\n}}\n}}\n\n'''Lee Sun-mi''' (born '''Sun Mi''' on May 2, 1992), known mononymously as '''Sunmi''', is a South Korean singer and songwriter. She debuted in 2007 as a member of South Korean girl group [[Wonder Girls]] and left the group in January 2010 to pursue an academic career. After a three-year long hiatus from the music scene, Sunmi resumed her career as a soloist in August 2013 with her debut extended play [[Full Moon (Sunmi EP)|''Full Moon'']], which spawned the number two singles \"24 Hours\" and \"Full Moon\" on South Korea's [[Gaon Digital Chart]].\n\nIn 2015, Sunmi was announced to be resuming promotion with the Wonder Girls until their disbandment in 2017. She subsequently left [[JYP Entertainment]] and joined Makeus Entertainment. Her second extended play [[Warning (Sunmi EP)|''Warning'']] was released in 2018 and produced the hit singles \"[[Gashina]]\", \"[[Heroine (Sunmi song)|Heroine]]\" and \"[[Siren (Sunmi song)|Siren]]\".\n\n==Early life==\nSun Mi was born on May 2, 1992 in [[Iksan]], [[Jeollabuk-do|North Jeolla]], South Korea.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.scmp.com/culture/music/article/2166002/sunmi-ex-wonder-girls-star-who-one-k-pops-most-famous-female-singers|title=Sunmi, the ex-Wonder Girl and K-pop's most bankable female star|date=September 29, 2018|website=South China Morning Post|language=en|access-date=June 15, 2019}}</ref> She attended Hwangnam Elementary School, Chungdam Middle School and [[Chungdam High School]] and attended [[Dongguk University]], majoring in musical theater. She adopted her stepfather's surname, Lee, while in university and merged her original given name and surname, becoming Lee Sun-mi.{{Citation needed|date=June 2019}}\n\n==Career==\n===2006\u20132017: Career beginnings, hiatus, and solo debut===\n{{multiple image\n| align = right\n| image1 = 2013 Sunmi02.jpg\n| width1 = 150\n| alt1 = \n| caption1 = \n| image2 = 141024 \ubcf4\uadf8\ud328\uc158\ub098\uc787\uc544\uc6c3\uc120\ubbf8 by \uc548\uc4f0 6.jpg\n| width2 = 150\n| alt2 = \n| caption2 = \n| footer = Sunmi in 2013 and 2014\n}}\n\nIn May 2006, Sunmi was revealed as a fourth member of [[Wonder Girls]], a girl group managed by [[JYP Entertainment]]. The group debuted with the single \"Irony\", on [[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]]'s ''[[Show! Music Core]]'' on February 10, 2007.{{citation needed|date=May 2018}} The group quickly rose to stardom with their hits \"Tell Me\", \"So Hot\" and \"Nobody\" within two years of debuting.{{citation needed|date=May 2018}} In January 2010, JYP announced that Sunmi would be postponing her musical career to pursue her academic career, but would continue until February in order to complete scheduled events.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/culture/2010/01/135_59552.html|title=Sunmi to Quit Wonder Girls|date=January 23, 2010|website=The Korea Times}}</ref> On January 13, 2012, A JYP representative stated, \"Sunmi has remained within the company and continues to sharpen her musical talents.\" JYP Entertainment later stated that there are no plans for Sunmi to return and comeback as a member of Wonder Girls.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20130820000792&ACE_SEARCH=1|title=No regrets leaving would be a lie: Ex-Wonder Girl Sunmi|date=August 20, 2013|website=The Korea Herald}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2013, Sunmi was announced to be returning to her music career, debuting as a solo artist.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20130806000595&ACE_SEARCH=1|title=Ex-Wonder Girls member Sunmi to make solo comeback|date=August 6, 2013|website=The Korea Herald}}</ref> Sunmi made her official debut stage on August 22, on [[Mnet (TV channel)|Mnet]]'s ''[[M! Countdown]]''. Her debut single \"[[Full Moon (Sunmi EP)|24 Hours]]\" was released on August 26, 2013; and subsequently achieved an all-kill on music charts.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=2976710|title='All kill' for ex-Wonder Girl|date=August 28, 2013|website=Korea JoongAng Daily}}</ref> Subsequently, her debut [[extended play]] (EP) ''[[Full Moon (Sunmi EP)|Full Moon]]'' was released on February 17, 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20140203000839&ACE_SEARCH=1|title=Sunmi to release debut EP this month|date=February 3, 2014|website=The Korea Herald}}</ref> The lead single peaked at number two on the Gaon Digital Chart<ref>{{cite web|title=2014\ub144 09\uc8fc\ucc28 Digital Chart|url=http://www.gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=ALL&targetTime=09&hitYear=2014&termGbn=week|website=Gaon|accessdate=February 9, 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150209131609/http://www.gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=ALL&targetTime=09&hitYear=2014&termGbn=week|archivedate=February 9, 2015|language=Korean}}</ref> and at number three on ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]''<nowiki>'</nowiki>s K-pop Hot 100.<ref>{{cite web|title=Korea K-Pop Hot 100 Week of March 8, 2014|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/k-pop-hot-100/2014-03-08|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Eldridge Industries]]|accessdate=February 9, 2015}}</ref> \"Full Moon\" was praised for being innovative, and Sunmi was said to have delivered a classy rendition of \"sexy\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20140221001132&ACE_SEARCH=1|title=Eyelike: Sunmi brings back 'sexy' with 'Full Moon'|date=February 21, 2014|website=The Korea Herald}}</ref>\n\nOn June 24, 2015, JYP Entertainment announced that Sunmi would be re-joining Wonder Girls, after withdrawing in 2010, for their comeback after the group's two-year hiatus. The group returned with a band concept, with Sunmi playing the [[Bass (instrument)|bass]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Ho-jung|first1=Won|title=Wonder Girls confirmed to return as band|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201506250933404661012_2|website=Kpop Herald|publisher=The Korea Herald|accessdate=June 25, 2015|date=June 24, 2015}}</ref> In August, the group's album ''[[Reboot (Wonder Girls album)|Reboot]]'' was released, with Sunmi co-writing and co-producing three of its tracks.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201507291805138254853_2&ACE_SEARCH=1|title=Wonder Girls unveil track list for 'Reboot'|date=July 29, 2015|website=Kpop Herald}}</ref> In 2016, Sunmi once again received songwriting and producing credits for a Wonder Girls release, this time for two songs present on the band's single album ''[[Why So Lonely]]'', including the title track of the same name.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mwave.interest.me/en/kpop-news/article/106390/wonder-girls-to-release-first-self-produced-album-kpop-girl-groups|title=Wonder Girls to Release First Self-Produced Album|date=June 24, 2016|website=enewsWorld|access-date=August 26, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170827045608/http://mwave.interest.me/en/kpop-news/article/106390/wonder-girls-to-release-first-self-produced-album-kpop-girl-groups|archive-date=August 27, 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n===2017\u2013present: Departure from JYP Entertainment, ''Warning'' and world tour===\nOn January 26, 2017, it was announced that Wonder Girls were to disband after unsuccessful contract renewal negotiation with members Yeeun and Sunmi. The group released their final single, \"[[Draw Me]]\", on February 10, 2017; it also served as a celebration for their tenth anniversary.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=3029179|title=After nearly ten years, Wonder Girls disband|date=January 21, 2017|accessdate=February 24, 2017|website=[[Korea JoongAng Daily]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201702091648266260163_2|title=Cover image for final single features Wonder Girls in watercolors|date=February 9, 2017|website=Kpop Herald|accessdate=February 24, 2017}}</ref> In March 2017, Sunmi signed with Makeus Entertainment. In August 2017, she released her single titled \"[[Gashina]]\", produced by [[Teddy Park]] of [[YG Entertainment|The Black Label]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=3037437|title=Sunmi drops experimental single|date=August 23, 2017|website=Korea JoongAng Daily}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://english.yonhapnews.co.kr/search1/2603000000.html?cid=AEN20170822006900315|title=EX-Wonder Girls' Sunmi makes solo comeback with 'Gashina|date=August 22, 2017|website=Yonhap News Agency}}</ref>\n\nSunmi returned with a single titled \"[[Heroine (Sunmi song)|Heroine]]\" on January 18, 2018. She described the single as a prequel to \"Gashina\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/8095083/sunmi-new-song-heroine-video-gashina-sequel|title=The Show Goes On With Sunmi's 'Gashina' Sequel 'Heroine' Despite Plagiarism Concerns|last=Herman|first=Tamar|date=January 19, 2018|website=Billboard|publisher=Eldridge Industries|access-date=May 9, 2018}}</ref> On September 4, 2018, Sunmi released her second EP titled ''[[Warning (Sunmi EP)|Warning]]'' along with the lead single \"Siren\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201809041758536207467_2&ACE_SEARCH=1|title=Sunmi returns with seductive yet dangerous 'Warning'|date=September 4, 2018|website=Kpop Herald}}</ref> \"Siren\" received an all-kill on six local music charts.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201809051054099067051_2&ACE_SEARCH=1|title=Sunmi dominates music charts with 'Siren'|date=September 5, 2018|website=Kpop Herald}}</ref> In February 2019, Sunmi held her first world tour titled \"Warning\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/8493738/sunmi-warning-world-tour-north-american-dates|title=Sunmi Announces 'Warning' World Tour: See the North American Dates|website=Billboard|access-date=September 26, 2019}}</ref> In the midst of the tour, on March 4, 2019, Sunmi released a single titled \"[[Noir (song)|Noir]]\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.philstar.com/entertainment/2019/03/15/1901478/k-pop-queen-sunmi-new-song-noir|title=K-pop queen Sunmi on new song Noir|website=philstar.com|access-date=March 15, 2019}}</ref> After completing the world tour she released her single \"Lalalay\" on August 27, 2019.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Jung |first1=Hae-myoung |title=K-pop diva Sunmi dominates music charts with 'Lalalay' |url=https://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/art/2019/08/732_274702.html |website=Korea Times |accessdate=January 22, 2020 |date=August 28, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn February 6, 2020, the music video for Sunmi's OST \"Gotta Go\" for the [[MBC TV|MBC]] web drama [[XX (web series)|XX]] was released.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tvreport.co.kr/2030853|title=\uc6f9\ub4dc\ub77c\ub9c8 '\uc5d1\uc2a4\uc5d1\uc2a4', \uc120\ubbf8\u2192\uc801\uc7ac OST \ub77c\uc778\uc5c5 \uacf5\uac1c|website=TV\ub9ac\ud3ec\ud2b8|access-date=February 7, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Discography ==\n{{See also|Wonder Girls discography}}\n\n===Extended plays===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of extended plays, with selected chart positions and sales\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:8em;\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:18em;\" | Details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"2\" | Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Sales\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"|[[Gaon Music Chart|KOR]]<br/><ref>Gaon Weekly Album Chart\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/album.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=&targetTime=09&hitYear=2014&termGbn=week|title=Full Moon - 2014\ub144 09\uc8fc\ucc28 Album Chart|work=Gaon Music Chart|publisher=Korea Music Content Industry Association|language=ko|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150209130832/http://www.gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/album.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=&targetTime=09&hitYear=2014&termGbn=week|archivedate=February 9, 2015}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/album.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=&targetTime=36&hitYear=2018&termGbn=week|title=Warning - 2018\ub144 36\uc8fc\ucc28 Album Chart|work=Gaon Music Chart|publisher=Korea Music Content Industry Association|language=ko}}\n</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"|[[Billboard charts#Albums|US<br/>World]]<br/><ref>Billboard World Albums\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/world-albums/2014-03-08|title=Full Moon|date=March 8, 2018|publisher=Billboard Charts}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" | ''[[Full Moon (Sunmi EP)|Full Moon]]''\n|\n* Released: February 17, 2014\n* Label: [[JYP Entertainment]]\n* Formats: [[Compact disc|CD]], [[Music download|digital download]]\n| 12 || 12\n|\n* KOR: 5,394<ref>Cumulative sales fo